<li><i><a href="http://www.accesstoinsight.org/lib/study/truths.html" class="external text" title="http://www.accesstoinsight.org/lib/study/truths.html" rel="nofollow">The Four Noble Truths: A Study Guide</a></i> (by Thanissaro Bhikkhu)</li>
<li><i>Wings to Awakening <a href="http://www.accesstoinsight.org/lib/modern/wings/3h1.html" class="external text" title="http://www.accesstoinsight.org/lib/modern/wings/3h1.html" rel="nofollow">Section 3.H.i: The Four Noble Truths</a></i> (translated by Thanissaro Bhikkhu)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Talks given by Ajahn Sumedho:
<ul>
<li>At <a href="http://www.amaravati.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.amaravati.org/" rel="nofollow">Amaravati Monastery</a>'s web: <i><a href="http://www.amaravati.org/abm/english/documents/4noble2/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.amaravati.org/abm/english/documents/4noble2/index.html" rel="nofollow">The Four Noble Truths</a></i></li>
<li>PDF version at <i><a href="http://www.buddhanet.net/" class="external text" title="http://www.buddhanet.net/" rel="nofollow">Buddhanet.net</a></i>: <i><a href="http://www.buddhanet.net/filelib/pdf/4nobltru.zip" class="external text" title="http://www.buddhanet.net/filelib/pdf/4nobltru.zip" rel="nofollow">The Four Noble Truths eBook</a></i></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>From the <a href="http://www.bodhimonastery.net/courses/TenLectures/TenLectures.html" class="external text" title="http://www.bodhimonastery.net/courses/TenLectures/TenLectures.html" rel="nofollow">Ten Lecture Series</a>, Lecture on the Four Noble Truths by Bhikkhu Bodhi: <i><a href="http://www.bodhimonastery.net/courses/TenLectures/MP3/BB-002_%20Four_Noble_Truths.mp3" class="external text" title="http://www.bodhimonastery.net/courses/TenLectures/MP3/BB-002_%20Four_Noble_Truths.mp3" rel="nofollow">The Four Noble Truths</a></i></li>
<li><a href="http://viewonbuddhism.org/4_noble_truths.html" class="external text" title="http://viewonbuddhism.org/4_noble_truths.html" rel="nofollow">A View on the Four Noble Truths</a></li>
<li><a href="http://myweb.cableone.net/subru/Buddhism.html" class="external text" title="http://myweb.cableone.net/subru/Buddhism.html" rel="nofollow"><i>The Light of Asia (Book Eight)</i></a>, a poem in <a href="/wiki/Iambic_pentameter" title="Iambic pentameter">iambic pentameter</a> by <a href="/wiki/Sir_Edwin_Arnold" title="Sir Edwin Arnold" class="mw-redirect">Sir Edwin Arnold</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mettanet.net/tipitaka/2Sutta-Pitaka/3Samyutta-Nikaya/Samyutta5/55-Sacca-Samyutta/02-Dhammacakkappavattanavaggo-p.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.mettanet.net/tipitaka/2Sutta-Pitaka/3Samyutta-Nikaya/Samyutta5/55-Sacca-Samyutta/02-Dhammacakkappavattanavaggo-p.htm" rel="nofollow">4 noble truths in pali</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.meditateinlondon.org.uk/buddhism-the-four-noble-truths.php" class="external text" title="http://www.meditateinlondon.org.uk/buddhism-the-four-noble-truths.php" rel="nofollow">Buddhism - the Four Noble Truths</a></li>
<li><i><a href="http://www.heartlandsangha.org/feeling.html" class="external text" title="http://www.heartlandsangha.org/feeling.html" rel="nofollow">The Feeling Buddha</a>:</i> An alternate interpretation of the Four Noble Truths.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.berzinarchives.com/sutra/sutra_level_4/list_16_4_noble_truths.html" class="external text" title="http://www.berzinarchives.com/sutra/sutra_level_4/list_16_4_noble_truths.html" rel="nofollow">Sixteen Aspects of the Four Noble Truths</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.nirvanasutra.org.uk" class="external text" title="http://www.nirvanasutra.org.uk" rel="nofollow">Nirvana Sutra</a>, for full text of the <i>Mahaparinirvana Sutra</i> and link to other tathagatagarbha sutras (including the <i>Angulimaliya Sutra</i>).</li>
</ul>
